1
00:00:10,860 --> 00:00:12,780
♪The wind blows, but I don't see you♪

2
00:00:12,820 --> 00:00:14,740
♪I added a few more strokes♪

3
00:00:14,740 --> 00:00:17,380
♪To the ending♪

4
00:00:17,580 --> 00:00:21,580
♪With the flowers falling
and the time passing♪

5
00:00:21,860 --> 00:00:24,140
♪Leaving only memories behind♪

6
00:00:24,300 --> 00:00:28,220
♪The wind blows from a long distance♪

7
00:00:28,340 --> 00:00:31,020
♪Yet, you didn't show up♪

8
00:00:31,140 --> 00:00:33,140
♪This love is full of regrets♪

9
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:37,420
♪You are but a dream
in this fleeting life♪

10
00:00:40,260 --> 00:00:41,260
[Part For Ever]

11
00:00:41,260 --> 00:00:42,000
[Adapted from a novel by Jing Mo,]

12
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:42,900
[My Lord,
Madam Doesn't Want to See You Again]

13
00:00:42,900 --> 00:00:44,780
[Episode 13]

14
00:00:44,780 --> 00:00:50,260
[Muxi Pavilion]

15
00:00:53,640 --> 00:00:56,150
Congratulations for
finding your ideal match, sir.

16
00:00:56,350 --> 00:00:57,750
The match is successful.

17
00:00:58,380 --> 00:01:04,900
♪I think of you again
as I write down the past memories♪

18
00:01:06,710 --> 00:01:07,510
Wan'er,

19
00:01:07,840 --> 00:01:08,920
I knew it was you.

20
00:01:09,810 --> 00:01:10,590
Congratulations!

21
00:01:10,590 --> 00:01:11,630
Congratulations!

22
00:01:12,430 --> 00:01:13,230
Let's go.

23
00:01:16,410 --> 00:01:17,720
Congratulations!

24
00:01:18,100 --> 00:01:23,780
♪This life is also tumultuous,
what use is there to confide in?♪

25
00:01:23,940 --> 00:01:31,260
♪The clear wind points to
the love and separation, so poignant♪

26
00:01:31,380 --> 00:01:38,100
♪As if you haven't left yet♪

27
00:01:45,430 --> 00:01:47,350
Miss, there's still room inside.

28
00:01:47,590 --> 00:01:48,400
Hold this.

29
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:50,120
Thank you.

30
00:01:50,480 --> 00:01:51,310
You are welcome, Miss.

31
00:01:56,040 --> 00:01:56,870
Thank you.

32
00:02:00,840 --> 00:02:01,870
You are welcome, Miss.

33
00:02:08,470 --> 00:02:09,310
Ling,

34
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:10,960
we really are destined for each other.

35
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:11,590
A match made in heaven.

36
00:02:11,590 --> 00:02:13,150
Candied haws!

37
00:02:13,870 --> 00:02:15,030
There's a candied fruits booth.

38
00:02:15,030 --> 00:02:16,120
Let's go and buy one.

39
00:02:18,190 --> 00:02:19,240
Have a look, Miss.

40
00:02:19,240 --> 00:02:19,910
Wan'er,

41
00:02:20,310 --> 00:02:21,360
You want some candied haws too?

42
00:02:21,630 --> 00:02:22,470
I'll get you some.

43
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:23,590
It's fine.

44
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:25,470
It's too sour for me.

45
00:02:25,840 --> 00:02:27,280
Let's go have some rice cakes.

46
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:28,560
Sure.

47
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:29,190
Here.

48
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:30,310
Do you remember
when we used to stroll through

49
00:02:30,310 --> 00:02:31,240
the market together as kids?

50
00:02:31,240 --> 00:02:32,870
You used to get rice cake
all over your face.

51
00:02:33,310 --> 00:02:35,360
Candied haws are sweet and sour,

52
00:02:35,630 --> 00:02:37,240
unlike sticky rice cake
that would get stuck in teeth

53
00:02:37,750 --> 00:02:38,870
and is hard to get rid of.

54
00:02:39,750 --> 00:02:41,680
I made some refreshing
sweet porridge today.

55
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:42,750
It pairs perfectly

56
00:02:42,750 --> 00:02:43,560
with these candied haws.

57
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:44,240
It's good.

58
00:02:44,240 --> 00:02:45,430
I'm a little tired.

59
00:02:45,430 --> 00:02:46,470
Let's go home.

60
00:02:46,630 --> 00:02:48,080
All right. Let's go.

61
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:09,960
Could it be that you have really

62
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:11,150
fallen in love with her?

63
00:03:13,030 --> 00:03:14,120
It's time to put the grudges

64
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:15,870
of the past generation behind you.

65
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:17,310
No.

66
00:03:17,470 --> 00:03:19,150
I don't have any feelings for him.

67
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:23,150
Grudges are grudges.

68
00:03:25,590 --> 00:03:27,560
I won't fall for you.

69
00:03:31,860 --> 00:03:37,060
♪Strong liquor cannot
dispel the melancholy of love♪

70
00:03:37,660 --> 00:03:43,260
♪The green mountains form a line
and the river reflects the moon♪

71
00:03:43,740 --> 00:03:48,780
♪Time flies like an arrow,
what day is today?♪

72
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:55,590
Wan'er...

73
00:03:55,660 --> 00:04:00,420
♪This love only awaits
your reciprocation♪

74
00:04:02,470 --> 00:04:04,430
Since you have no feelings for me,

75
00:04:05,430 --> 00:04:07,150
why do you still come to me?

76
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:10,800
Leave.

77
00:04:14,910 --> 00:04:15,870
Ling...

78
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:19,720
You're drunk.

79
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:23,680
Yes.

80
00:04:24,680 --> 00:04:26,070
I'm drunk.

81
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:54,510
Ling,

82
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:56,160
I know you love me,

83
00:04:56,830 --> 00:04:57,830
I love you too.

84
00:04:59,620 --> 00:05:06,180
♪The lonely goose cries in sorrow♪

85
00:05:07,100 --> 00:05:14,220
♪Life passes quickly,
like how dusk arrives suddenly♪

86
00:05:15,020 --> 00:05:20,820
♪The evening snowy wind is too strong
that the boat cannot sail♪

87
00:05:20,940 --> 00:05:28,300
♪The peach blossom falls on my bed
the moon is as bright as ever♪

88
00:05:28,920 --> 00:05:30,680
Since I can't win over your love,

89
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:32,830
I will...

90
00:05:35,860 --> 00:05:39,380
♪Not going back, not looking back♪

91
00:05:39,620 --> 00:05:43,940
♪Even good times are spent in vain♪

92
00:05:44,700 --> 00:05:49,260
♪Trapped in the mornings
and the evenings♪

93
00:05:50,340 --> 00:05:57,700
♪As the flames of live extinguish,
it's all nothingness in the end♪

94
00:05:57,980 --> 00:06:05,340
♪Asking why you are looking forward
to the summer and the winter♪

95
00:06:05,420 --> 00:06:13,620
♪A handful of soil, fate is sealed,
sighing over twilight♪

96
00:06:14,580 --> 00:06:21,180
♪No one shows up♪

97
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:45,510
Ling,

98
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:46,950
you're awake.

99
00:06:47,830 --> 00:06:48,750
What are you doing here?

100
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:50,680
I...

101
00:06:51,310 --> 00:06:52,070
Ling,

102
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:54,750
don't blame yourself.

103
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:56,630
I did it willingly.

104
00:06:59,680 --> 00:07:00,560
Ling,

105
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:02,310
we've known each other since childhood,

106
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:03,950
and we've always admired each other.

107
00:07:04,270 --> 00:07:06,310
It's my choice to become your woman.

108
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:09,310
I don't care about status

109
00:07:09,310 --> 00:07:10,070
or wealth,

110
00:07:10,630 --> 00:07:12,830
I just want to stay
by your side forever.

111
00:07:14,070 --> 00:07:14,920
No way.

112
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:16,480
You really think I'm that gullible?

113
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:21,870
You'll be mine sooner or later.

114
00:07:59,430 --> 00:08:00,240
What's wrong?

115
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:01,750
Since you came back last night,

116
00:08:02,070 --> 00:08:03,360
you've been feeling down.

117
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:08,070
I was drawn by the splendor
of the Lantern Festival last night

118
00:08:08,510 --> 00:08:09,680
and couldn't resist lingering.

119
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:11,830
Now I realize

120
00:08:12,070 --> 00:08:13,070
that no matter how lively it is,

121
00:08:13,270 --> 00:08:14,240
it's

122
00:08:14,510 --> 00:08:16,310
all fleeting.

123
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:20,560
Clouds disperse easily,
and glass shatters.

124
00:08:20,830 --> 00:08:22,070
It's the same thing.

125
00:08:23,270 --> 00:08:24,240
But rest assured,

126
00:08:24,430 --> 00:08:25,560
no matter what happens,

127
00:08:25,870 --> 00:08:27,310
I will always be by your side.

128
00:08:27,950 --> 00:08:30,270
I didn't expect you to be so hospitable,

129
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:36,150
receiving a guest

130
00:08:36,390 --> 00:08:39,550
in the garden early in the morning.

131
00:08:39,910 --> 00:08:41,480
This is nothing
compared to you, My Lord,

132
00:08:41,790 --> 00:08:43,910
wearing yourself out
for a lady last night,

133
00:08:44,270 --> 00:08:46,120
spending the whole night with her.

134
00:08:46,750 --> 00:08:47,630
Wan'er...

135
00:09:25,900 --> 00:09:31,580
♪Flowers fall in the courtyard,
a few branches of begonias bloom♪

136
00:09:33,540 --> 00:09:39,780
♪Playing the qin under the moon,
recalling his poem♪

137
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:41,240
Does it hurt?

138
00:09:41,300 --> 00:09:47,380
♪Grinding ink, feelings fill the paper♪

139
00:09:47,820 --> 00:09:53,860
♪Each stroke guides me into the play♪

140
00:09:58,270 --> 00:09:59,870
My business has nothing to do with you,

141
00:10:01,030 --> 00:10:02,630
and you shouldn't be here.

142
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,000
I will investigate

143
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,080
what happened last night

144
00:10:08,030 --> 00:10:09,030
and give you an explanation.

145
00:10:09,540 --> 00:10:12,580
♪The rain falls and
the begonias stir up lovesickness♪

146
00:10:12,960 --> 00:10:14,870
It's not me you need to explain to,

147
00:10:15,270 --> 00:10:16,510
it's Miss Niyue.

148
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:19,550
She's been with you for so many years.

149
00:10:20,150 --> 00:10:21,720
It's time to give her a proper status.

150
00:10:22,150 --> 00:10:23,630
The matter hasn't been investigated yet.

151
00:10:23,870 --> 00:10:25,240
There's no need to jump to conclusions.

152
00:10:28,790 --> 00:10:30,840
Your private affairs
are none of my concern,

153
00:10:31,510 --> 00:10:32,270
and I don't care

154
00:10:32,270 --> 00:10:34,080
what you did with someone else.

155
00:10:36,750 --> 00:10:37,870
Do you wish

156
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:40,480
something happened between me and Niyue?

157
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:41,510
No.

158
00:10:52,870 --> 00:10:54,120
I hope you can

159
00:10:54,870 --> 00:10:56,720
take responsibility.

160
00:10:57,750 --> 00:10:58,870
Marry

161
00:10:59,750 --> 00:11:01,120
Miss Niyue,

162
00:11:02,670 --> 00:11:03,960
and live a happy life together.

163
00:11:10,940 --> 00:11:17,420
♪Grinding ink, feelings fill the paper♪

164
00:11:18,020 --> 00:11:23,940
♪Each stroke guides me into the play♪

165
00:11:25,380 --> 00:11:28,620
♪Years have passed, the flowers
have bloomed again♪

166
00:11:29,020 --> 00:11:32,460
♪In this life without you,
day and night feel endless♪

167
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:36,020
♪In this old dreamland,
memories of past lives are locked away♪

168
00:11:36,140 --> 00:11:39,380
♪I didn't see you when I woke up and
opened the windows♪

169
00:11:39,460 --> 00:11:42,820
♪The rain falls and
the begonias stir up lovesickness♪

170
00:11:42,900 --> 00:11:46,500
♪No one knows how much I miss you♪

171
00:11:46,620 --> 00:11:50,460
♪The wind from my hometown has arrived♪

172
